67
00:04:17,823 --> 00:04:20,826
I'm the official interface
between the police department

68
00:04:20,826 --> 00:04:22,413
and the TAC, you know.

69
00:04:22,413 --> 00:04:23,414
So, as a show of mutual respect,

70
00:04:23,414 --> 00:04:27,251
why don't you come see a
movie with me and we'll...

71
00:04:27,251 --> 00:04:30,463
So, is that why
you asked me here?

72
00:04:30,463 --> 00:04:31,213
(Shunichi laughing)

73
00:04:31,213 --> 00:04:33,591
Wanna hear an
Aragami phone call?

74
00:04:33,591 --> 00:04:34,883
What?

75
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:38,983
The Aragami?

76
00:04:39,084 --> 00:04:43,084
- [Aragami] Mr.
Kijima, I know you love

77
00:04:43,084 --> 00:04:44,352
your child very much.

78
00:04:44,352 --> 00:04:46,852
If you want to prevent
her death from occurring,

79
00:04:46,852 --> 00:04:49,855
you will open the files
on the Kushinada Project

80
00:04:49,855 --> 00:04:51,983
to the general public.

81
00:04:51,983 --> 00:04:52,858
(Momiji gasping)

82
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:56,860
The Kushinada Project?

83
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:58,240
- [Aragami] In two days time,

84
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,368
you will place a full
page advertisement

85
00:05:00,368 --> 00:05:02,578
in Tokyo's five
biggest newspapers

86
00:05:02,578 --> 00:05:05,581
using the code name
Japan Pottery Union.

87
00:05:05,581 --> 00:05:06,873
The ad will detail
the production process

88
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:10,973
for the ceramic that blocks
the power of the Kushinada.

89
00:05:10,973 --> 00:05:12,338
(Momiji gasping)
What?

90
00:05:12,338 --> 00:05:15,383
I can't do that.

91
00:05:15,383 --> 00:05:17,050
(Mrs. Kijima crying)

92
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:17,883
Oh, no.

93
00:05:17,883 --> 00:05:20,179
Oh detective, what
are we gonna do?

94
00:05:20,179 --> 00:05:22,848
- [Detective] We'll investigate
this matter as best we can.

95
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:26,870
For now, you gotta have
faith in us and the TAC.

96
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:30,970
(Mrs. Kijima crying)

97
00:05:31,969 --> 00:05:35,969
Well?

98
00:05:35,969 --> 00:05:37,738
- [Azusa] It's
Aragami all right.

99
00:05:37,738 --> 00:05:39,948
We found a very amount
of Aragami tissue

100
00:05:39,948 --> 00:05:42,075
on the window seal.

101
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:46,175
It's really them.

102
00:05:46,175 --> 00:05:49,915
She's supposed to be
starting school soon.

103
00:05:49,915 --> 00:05:53,379
Mr. Kunikida, what is
the Kushinada Project?

104
00:05:53,379 --> 00:05:54,045
Hm?
Huh?

105
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:58,145
The project has something to
do with me, doesn't it, sir?

106
00:05:58,145 --> 00:06:01,429
Please tell her.

107
00:06:01,529 --> 00:06:05,529
I've told you that you have
a twin sister, haven't I?

108
00:06:05,529 --> 00:06:09,311
You mean Kaede, right?

109
00:06:09,311 --> 00:06:11,187
Prior to the return
of the Aragami,

110
00:06:11,187 --> 00:06:12,939
the Science and
Technology Agency

111
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,401
began a special
research project.

112
00:06:15,401 --> 00:06:18,237
Using Kaede, who was
then the Kushinada,

113
00:06:18,237 --> 00:06:20,946
we tried to control the Aragami.

114
00:06:20,946 --> 00:06:22,991
That was the Kushinada Project.

115
00:06:22,991 --> 00:06:25,951
The TAC was given
total control of it.

116
00:06:25,951 --> 00:06:28,037
We ran batteries
of tests on Kaede,

117
00:06:28,037 --> 00:06:31,417
trying to determine what
made the Kushinadas unique.

118
00:06:31,417 --> 00:06:33,419
In the process, we
accidentally discovered

119
00:06:33,419 --> 00:06:35,003
that a particular
type of ceramic

120
00:06:35,003 --> 00:06:38,382
could actually contain the
power of the Kushinada.

121
00:06:38,382 --> 00:06:40,966
Utilizing this ceramic,
we hope to be able

122
00:06:40,966 --> 00:06:42,177
to store the Kushinada's power

123
00:06:42,177 --> 00:06:44,430
for use as a weapon
against the Aragami.

124
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:47,892
Unfortunately, it can also
be used by the Aragami

125
00:06:47,992 --> 00:06:51,992
to protect themselves
from the Kushinada.

126
00:06:53,522 --> 00:06:57,522
Then somehow someone managed
to steal some of this substance

127
00:06:57,522 --> 00:07:00,987
without being noticed.

128
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:05,087
The next time we saw it was in
Izumo, where I first met you.

129
00:07:06,815 --> 00:07:10,815
(Momiji gasping)

130
00:07:10,815 --> 00:07:12,291
A Ceramic Field?

131
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:13,501
Orochi said something about that

132
00:07:13,501 --> 00:07:15,628
the first time I was attacked.

133
00:07:15,628 --> 00:07:16,462
That's right.

134
00:07:16,462 --> 00:07:18,422
So, Orochi stole this stuff?

135
00:07:18,422 --> 00:07:22,008
Perhaps, but there was no
evidence the Aragami took it.

136
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:24,762
It's far more likely that
someone in our organization

137
00:07:24,862 --> 00:07:28,862
stole the ceramic and then
sold it to the Aragami.

138
00:07:28,862 --> 00:07:31,016
An Aragami spy?

139
00:07:31,016 --> 00:07:32,770
The government was
afraid that someone

140
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:35,020
would use the substance
for the wrong purpose.

141
00:07:35,020 --> 00:07:38,023
So all of the data and remaining
samples were destroyed.

142
00:07:38,023 --> 00:07:40,694
- [Kusanagi] Now
it all makes sense.

143
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:41,445
- [Momiji] Kusanagi!

144
00:07:41,445 --> 00:07:43,322
I've been wondering
why the Aragami

145
00:07:43,322 --> 00:07:44,532
haven't attacked you lately.

146
00:07:44,532 --> 00:07:48,033
They must not have any of
that ceramic stuff left.

147
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:50,119
You were originally
on their side.

148
00:07:50,119 --> 00:07:52,080
Do you have any idea
what the Aragami

149
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:54,375
are trying to do this time?

150
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:56,209
I don't know.

151
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:58,337
Listen, Momiji, don't even think

152
00:07:58,337 --> 00:08:01,006
about getting involved
in this thing.

153
00:08:01,006 --> 00:08:01,423
Huh?

154
00:08:01,423 --> 00:08:04,009
- [Kusanagi] If the Aragami
can get their slimy tentacles

155
00:08:04,009 --> 00:08:05,260
on both you and the kid,

156
00:08:05,260 --> 00:08:06,971
they'll be no stopping them.

157
00:08:06,971 --> 00:08:07,555
Forget it.

158
00:08:07,555 --> 00:08:09,807
Don't you care about
that poor little girl?

159
00:08:09,807 --> 00:08:11,140
Why shouldn't I help?

160
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:11,976
You idiot!

161
00:08:11,976 --> 00:08:15,061
Think about how important you
are and the answer's obvious!

162
00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:16,647
Got that?

163
00:08:16,647 --> 00:08:17,063
Hold it!

164
00:08:17,063 --> 00:08:18,774
You're the idiot, not me!

165
00:08:18,774 --> 00:08:19,400
You stupid.

166
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:22,653
(Momiji screaming)

167
00:08:22,653 --> 00:08:24,446
(Kunikida sighing)

168
00:08:24,446 --> 00:08:26,657
Hm?

169
00:08:26,657 --> 00:08:27,115
Huh?

170
00:08:27,115 --> 00:08:31,077
The Chief Cabinet Secretary!

171
00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:33,747
This situation worries me.

172
00:08:33,747 --> 00:08:35,749
You know I cannot
allow the Kushinada

173
00:08:35,749 --> 00:08:37,793
to be placed in
any sort of danger.

174
00:08:37,879 --> 00:08:41,879
The Kushinada is our
trump card after all.

175
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:44,842
What about the girl?

176
00:08:44,842 --> 00:08:47,553
Mr. Kunikida, please
keep a close eye

177
00:08:47,553 --> 00:08:49,388
on the Kushinada's actions.

178
00:08:49,488 --> 00:08:53,488
And don't let your
emotions carry you away.

179
00:08:53,488 --> 00:08:57,102
I'll assign extra
detectives to this case.

180
00:08:57,102 --> 00:08:57,896
Stand aside.

181
00:08:57,896 --> 00:08:58,814
Let me through.

182
00:08:58,814 --> 00:09:00,399
It's all right, don't worry.

183
00:09:00,399 --> 00:09:04,109
Your husband has always been
a vital part of this project.

184
00:09:04,109 --> 00:09:07,112
I won't let them
abandon your daughter.

185
00:09:07,112 --> 00:09:08,323
That's Congressman Miyahara,

186
00:09:08,323 --> 00:09:12,117
one of the Kushinada
Project's top supporters.

187
00:09:12,117 --> 00:09:13,118
No matter what they say,

188
00:09:13,118 --> 00:09:15,120
the most important
thing is Yukiko's life.

189
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,791
Even if the data does get
revealed to the public,

190
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:20,376
the Aragami won't
defeat the TAC.

191
00:09:20,376 --> 00:09:21,126
That's right!

192
00:09:21,126 --> 00:09:24,965
I'll help you find her
no matter what happens.

193
00:09:24,965 --> 00:09:25,966
Momiji.

194
00:09:25,966 --> 00:09:26,717
I can't forgive this.

195
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:30,817
In order to get to me, they've
kidnapped an innocent child.

196
00:09:30,817 --> 00:09:34,433
You're the Kushinada?

197
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:35,559
I'm so sorry this happened,

198
00:09:35,559 --> 00:09:38,103
but no matter what happens
I'll find the culprits

199
00:09:38,203 --> 00:09:42,203
and make sure you
get Yukiko back.

200
00:09:43,178 --> 00:09:47,178
What a good girl, I trust you!

201
00:09:47,272 --> 00:09:51,272
Um, thanks.

202
00:09:51,272 --> 00:09:54,912
Man, this is gonna be a
real pain in the posterior.

203
00:09:54,912 --> 00:09:57,498
After the Kushinada
project was shut down,

204
00:09:57,498 --> 00:09:58,832
most of the staff were laid off

205
00:09:58,832 --> 00:10:00,125
or transferred to new positions.

206
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:03,045
Are you sure Momiji's
got to meet all of them?

207
00:10:03,045 --> 00:10:05,005
Her locator ability
is our best chance

208
00:10:05,005 --> 00:10:07,633
of finding the Aragami
who kidnapped Yukiko.

209
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:08,801
- [Yaegashi] I
understand that but...

210
00:10:08,801 --> 00:10:12,012
Mr. Yaegashi, this is the
best chance we've got.

211
00:10:12,012 --> 00:10:14,848
Please, just tell
me where to go.

212
00:10:14,848 --> 00:10:16,642
Sorry, ma'am.

213
00:10:16,642 --> 00:10:20,185
If you don't speed up,
she'll get really mad.

214
00:10:20,185 --> 00:10:21,229
- [Yaegashi] Okay, okay.

215
00:10:21,229 --> 00:10:22,187
The first name on the list

216
00:10:22,187 --> 00:10:25,651
is Professor Akahori
at Touto University.

217
00:10:25,751 --> 00:10:29,751
He's been with the university
since leaving the project.

218
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:39,368
Not him.

219
00:10:39,368 --> 00:10:42,375
- [Yaegashi] The next
stop is the TV station.

220
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,460
Ms. Marukawa who was an
assistant on the project

221
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:48,560
is now an assistant professor
and television personality.

222
00:10:49,118 --> 00:10:53,118
Huh?

223
00:10:53,118 --> 00:10:53,846
Mm-mm.

224
00:10:53,846 --> 00:10:55,931
- [Yaegashi] Next we have
the bacteriology department's

225
00:10:55,931 --> 00:10:59,143
fair-haired boy,
Assistant Professor Satou.

226
00:10:59,143 --> 00:11:01,061
He left the project
shortly after the theft

227
00:11:01,146 --> 00:11:05,146
on grounds of incompatibility
with his coworkers.

228
00:11:05,246 --> 00:11:09,246
(Momiji babbling)

229
00:11:11,308 --> 00:11:15,308
Are you all right?

230
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:19,408
- [Yaegashi] So, he
isn't one either?

231
00:11:20,985 --> 00:11:24,985
[Momiji Voiceover] I'm coming.

232
00:11:24,985 --> 00:11:28,005
I'm coming, Yukiko!

233
00:11:28,005 --> 00:11:31,256
(Momiji screaming)

234
00:11:31,256 --> 00:11:32,425
Momiji!

235
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:36,525
[Momiji Voiceover] I will
rescue you, no matter what.

236
00:11:40,893 --> 00:11:44,893
(soft music)

237
00:11:49,764 --> 00:11:53,764
I'm sorry, sir.

238
00:11:53,864 --> 00:11:57,864
We've wasted a lot of time
getting my leg examined.

239
00:11:57,864 --> 00:12:00,285
No, it's not your fault.

240
00:12:00,285 --> 00:12:02,998
It's because I was impatient.

241
00:12:02,998 --> 00:12:03,916
Hm.

242
00:12:03,916 --> 00:12:05,458
Let's get back to work.

243
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:06,291
Mr. Yaegashi,

244
00:12:06,291 --> 00:12:08,587
Mr. Yaegashi, who's
next on the list?

245
00:12:08,587 --> 00:12:11,296
(Momiji groaning)

246
00:12:11,296 --> 00:12:13,175
Don't overwork yourself!

247
00:12:13,175 --> 00:12:14,927
Don't worry, I'm fine.

248
00:12:14,927 --> 00:12:15,886
Momijji.

249
00:12:15,886 --> 00:12:17,302
No, really, I'm fine.

250
00:12:17,302 --> 00:12:20,891
Isn't that right, sir?

251
00:12:20,891 --> 00:12:21,642
Yaegashi, just hurry up

252
00:12:21,642 --> 00:12:25,310
and tell Momiji who's
next on the list.

253
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:26,354
We don't have much time.

254
00:12:26,354 --> 00:12:27,312
Let's go.

255
00:12:27,312 --> 00:12:28,857
Yes, sir.

256
00:12:28,857 --> 00:12:31,109
- [Yaegashi] Next up are
the government officials

257
00:12:31,109 --> 00:12:32,485
who promoted the project.

258
00:12:32,485 --> 00:12:33,904
The closest one to the hospital

259
00:12:34,004 --> 00:12:38,004
is Congressman Miyahara's place.

260
00:12:38,004 --> 00:12:39,284
Not the Congressman.

261
00:12:39,284 --> 00:12:40,576
Momiji already
cleared him, right?

262
00:12:40,576 --> 00:12:42,746
Right.
- [Yaegashi] I see.

263
00:12:42,746 --> 00:12:43,747
Well, then, let's see.

264
00:12:43,747 --> 00:12:45,249
The next one is.

265
00:12:45,249 --> 00:12:47,458
(Momiji gasping)

266
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:49,544
Huh?
Momiji.

267
00:12:49,544 --> 00:12:50,838
- [Yaegashi] We got something.

268
00:12:50,938 --> 00:12:54,938
Huh?

269
00:12:59,888 --> 00:13:03,888
(Yukiko sobbing)

270
00:13:08,217 --> 00:13:12,217
(Aragami laughing)

271
00:13:12,217 --> 00:13:15,112
How are you feeling,
little girl?

272
00:13:15,112 --> 00:13:16,487
Let me out of here!

273
00:13:16,487 --> 00:13:18,031
I'm cold and hungry.

274
00:13:18,031 --> 00:13:19,908
I'm getting hungry too,

275
00:13:19,908 --> 00:13:23,536
but I'm going to have
a delicious supper.

276
00:13:23,536 --> 00:13:26,414
I'm going to eat you!

277
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:30,514
Yummy!

278
00:13:31,376 --> 00:13:35,376
(Yukiko screaming)
(Aragami growling)

279
00:13:43,669 --> 00:13:47,669
(bell ringing)

280
00:13:47,669 --> 00:13:49,897
- [Narushima] Mr.
Kunikida, what is wrong?

281
00:13:49,897 --> 00:13:52,440
I'd like to get Mr.
Miyahara's opinion

282
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,649
on the current incident.

283
00:13:53,649 --> 00:13:55,400
- [Narushima] Yes, I understand.

284
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,653
I'll let Mr. Miyahara know.
Well?

285
00:13:57,653 --> 00:13:58,446
- [Miyahara] Help!

286
00:13:58,446 --> 00:13:59,404
Somebody help me!

287
00:13:59,404 --> 00:14:00,282
Monster, help me!

288
00:14:00,282 --> 00:14:02,284
Mr. Congressman.
What's wrong, sir?

289
00:14:02,284 --> 00:14:05,411
Narushima, my
assistant is a monster!

290
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:07,122
Ah?

291
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:11,222
(monster growling)

292
00:14:15,367 --> 00:14:19,367
Wait for me, sir.

293
00:14:19,367 --> 00:14:20,719
Momiji, you're injured!

294
00:14:20,719 --> 00:14:23,221
Leave the rest of this to us.

295
00:14:23,221 --> 00:14:23,638
But...

296
00:14:23,638 --> 00:14:25,430
You've already
found the Aragami.

297
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:28,101
Now let us take care of our end.

298
00:14:28,101 --> 00:14:28,517
But...

299
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:32,617
That's an order
from your superior.

300
00:14:38,347 --> 00:14:42,347
Congressman Miyahara
was pretty surprised

301
00:14:42,347 --> 00:14:44,449
to learn that his own
secretary was an Aragami

302
00:14:44,451 --> 00:14:48,451
but unfortunately we still
haven't found Yukiko yet.

303
00:14:48,451 --> 00:14:49,538
Did you look everywhere?

304
00:14:49,538 --> 00:14:52,457
We searched all over
Mr. Miyahara's house,

305
00:14:52,457 --> 00:14:54,459
with his full cooperation.

306
00:14:54,459 --> 00:14:56,629
But still once we
catch an Aragami,

307
00:14:56,629 --> 00:15:00,133
we ought to be able to
find her pretty quickly.

308
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:03,469
Maybe it's not an Aragami.

309
00:15:03,469 --> 00:15:05,889
I felt something
different this time,

310
00:15:05,989 --> 00:15:09,989
something much
much more powerful.

311
00:15:18,264 --> 00:15:22,264
Kusanagi, hello?

312
00:15:22,364 --> 00:15:26,364
Are you there?

313
00:15:26,364 --> 00:15:28,661
He's not here.

314
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:32,761
I'll have to do this myself.

315
00:15:36,169 --> 00:15:40,169
(Momiji screaming)

316
00:15:40,257 --> 00:15:44,257
(Miyahara laughing)

317
00:15:44,257 --> 00:15:46,054
I knew it, it is you!

318
00:15:46,054 --> 00:15:48,764
- [Miyahara] And
I knew you'd come.

319
00:15:48,764 --> 00:15:50,392
You're a brave girl.

320
00:15:50,392 --> 00:15:53,979
Quite suitable to
be the Kushinada.

321
00:15:53,979 --> 00:15:57,522
Why didn't I feel anything
the first time that we met?

322
00:15:57,522 --> 00:15:58,733
(Miyahara laughing)

323
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:02,833
These are the last bits of
the original Ceramic Field.

324
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:07,280
By covering my mitama, I can
deceive you quite easily.

325
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:10,703
Monster!

326
00:16:10,703 --> 00:16:13,664
Crying won't help
you but go ahead.

327
00:16:13,664 --> 00:16:16,043
I enjoy the sound.

328
00:16:16,143 --> 00:16:20,143
(Miyahara laughing evilly)

329
00:16:22,090 --> 00:16:26,090
Goodness, what a nice
little toy you have there!

330
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:29,222
Give Yukiko back to me!

331
00:16:29,222 --> 00:16:31,224
- [Miyahara] How ironic!

332
00:16:31,224 --> 00:16:33,559
I was the one who
raised the most protest

333
00:16:33,561 --> 00:16:37,561
against using you as
a human sacrifice.

334
00:16:37,561 --> 00:16:38,273
Liar!

335
00:16:38,273 --> 00:16:39,983
But of course, that
was because we Aragami

336
00:16:39,983 --> 00:16:43,445
would have been extremely
inconvenienced by your death.

337
00:16:43,445 --> 00:16:44,905
But that problem will be solved

338
00:16:44,905 --> 00:16:46,571
when we get more of the ceramic.

339
00:16:46,636 --> 00:16:50,636
How sad for you and nice for us.

340
00:16:50,636 --> 00:16:51,744
Give her back!

341
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:54,579
(gun shooting)

342
00:16:54,579 --> 00:16:57,167
(Miyahara laughing)

343
00:16:57,267 --> 00:17:01,267
(Momiji screaming)

344
00:17:05,371 --> 00:17:09,371
Yukiko, I'm sorry.

345
00:17:09,371 --> 00:17:11,264
(gun shooting)
(Aragami groaning)

346
00:17:11,264 --> 00:17:12,848
Kome, we need him alive.

347
00:17:12,848 --> 00:17:14,017
I know that.

348
00:17:14,017 --> 00:17:15,643
You're no fun at all.

349
00:17:15,643 --> 00:17:17,770
He's still moving.

350
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:20,605
(Aragami growling)

351
00:17:20,605 --> 00:17:22,526
That's better.

352
00:17:22,526 --> 00:17:24,777
All right, tell us
where the hostage is

353
00:17:24,777 --> 00:17:26,611
or we're gonna have to hurt you.

354
00:17:26,711 --> 00:17:30,711
(Aragami laughing)

355
00:17:30,711 --> 00:17:34,619
(all coughing)

356
00:17:34,619 --> 00:17:36,540
Mr. Kunikida, Takeuchi here.

357
00:17:36,540 --> 00:17:40,001
The Aragami we were chasing
just blew itself up.

358
00:17:40,001 --> 00:17:42,504
- [Kunikida] I've
got bad news too.

359
00:17:42,504 --> 00:17:43,796
Momiji's missing.

360
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:44,464
What?

361
00:17:44,564 --> 00:17:48,564
Momiji's gone?
Huh?

362
00:17:51,636 --> 00:17:55,636
Is it evening already?

363
00:17:55,636 --> 00:17:58,894
What the heck is this place?

364
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:02,994
A Transylvanian castle?

365
00:18:02,994 --> 00:18:05,734
Too high.

366
00:18:05,734 --> 00:18:08,779
This is ridiculous.

367
00:18:08,779 --> 00:18:11,158
Huh?

368
00:18:11,158 --> 00:18:12,242
Yukiko.

369
00:18:12,242 --> 00:18:15,036
You are Yukiko, aren't you?

370
00:18:15,036 --> 00:18:18,706
I came here to rescue you, but.

371
00:18:18,706 --> 00:18:20,000
- [Yukiko] I want to go home!

372
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,751
I want to see my
mommy and daddy.

373
00:18:22,751 --> 00:18:23,668
(Yukiko crying)

374
00:18:23,668 --> 00:18:25,670
[Momiji Voiceover] They
took my communications unit.

375
00:18:25,670 --> 00:18:29,384
It'll be night soon,
and once it's night

376
00:18:29,384 --> 00:18:31,676
they're gonna eat me.

377
00:18:31,676 --> 00:18:33,972
Shh, don't worry!

378
00:18:34,072 --> 00:18:38,072
I won't let anything
hurt you, okay?

379
00:18:38,072 --> 00:18:41,770
- [Kunikida] This is Kunikida.

380
00:18:41,770 --> 00:18:44,357
Has there been any
change in the situation?

381
00:18:44,357 --> 00:18:46,026
No, not at the moment.

382
00:18:46,026 --> 00:18:46,985
Sir, I'm gonna go ahead

383
00:18:46,985 --> 00:18:49,404
and prepare the
advertisement for the paper.

384
00:18:49,404 --> 00:18:51,198
Just in case.

385
00:18:51,298 --> 00:18:55,298
[Kunikida Voiceover] 10 hours
before our time runs out.

386
00:18:55,298 --> 00:18:58,871
Is your leg okay, big sister?

387
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:02,971
Don't you worry, I'm fine.

388
00:19:03,738 --> 00:19:07,738
[Momiji Voiceover] If
we can get over there,

389
00:19:07,738 --> 00:19:10,383
we can use that
emergency ladder.

390
00:19:10,383 --> 00:19:12,385
It's the only way!

391
00:19:12,385 --> 00:19:14,638
Yukiko, ready?

392
00:19:14,638 --> 00:19:17,307
- [Aragami] What do
you thing you're doing?

393
00:19:17,307 --> 00:19:18,766
Hold on tight.

394
00:19:18,766 --> 00:19:20,725
(girls screaming)

395
00:19:20,825 --> 00:19:24,825
No, I won't let you get away.

396
00:19:25,148 --> 00:19:29,148
(girls screaming)

397
00:19:32,641 --> 00:19:36,641
Kusanagi!

398
00:19:36,641 --> 00:19:39,912
(Aragami growling)

399
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:40,913
Kusanagi?

400
00:19:40,913 --> 00:19:43,748
Momiji, what in the
heck are you doing here?

401
00:19:43,748 --> 00:19:46,419
- [Momiji] You answer
the same question!

402
00:19:46,419 --> 00:19:49,381
Kusanagi, you traitor!

403
00:19:49,381 --> 00:19:51,924
Didn't I tell you not
to get found with this?

404
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:56,024
I've been following
the Congressman
until he led me here.

405
00:19:56,024 --> 00:20:00,015
(Aragami growling)

406
00:20:00,015 --> 00:20:00,933
What are you doing here?

407
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:04,769
Momiji sent us a signal
with her tracking beacon.

408
00:20:04,769 --> 00:20:06,147
What?

409
00:20:06,147 --> 00:20:06,771
I was bugged.

410
00:20:06,771 --> 00:20:09,526
I had it hidden
inside my bandage.

411
00:20:09,526 --> 00:20:10,277
Okay, culprits.

412
00:20:10,277 --> 00:20:12,654
Let's commit a little heroicize.

413
00:20:12,654 --> 00:20:13,738
You got it!

414
00:20:13,738 --> 00:20:15,156
No, you don't.

415
00:20:15,256 --> 00:20:19,256
(upbeat music)
(Aragami growling)

416
00:20:40,709 --> 00:20:44,709
(Yukiko giggling)

417
00:20:44,709 --> 00:20:46,563
Thank you, Kusanagi.

418
00:20:46,565 --> 00:20:50,565
You planned on rescuing
Yukiko all along, didn't you?

419
00:20:50,565 --> 00:20:51,025
Heck no.

420
00:20:51,025 --> 00:20:53,068
Finding the kid was
just the easiest way

421
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:57,168
to find the Aragami.

422
00:20:57,168 --> 00:20:58,408
Hm.

423
00:20:58,408 --> 00:21:01,202
Don't ever go overboard
like this again, okay?

424
00:21:01,202 --> 00:21:02,036
Huh?

425
00:21:02,036 --> 00:21:04,079
A princess and a prince.

426
00:21:04,079 --> 00:21:07,417
Don't they make a
lovely couple, Ryouko?

427
00:21:07,417 --> 00:21:07,833
What?

428
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:08,833
Just what are you saying?

429
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,835
Oh, your little cheeks
are turning red!

430
00:21:10,835 --> 00:21:12,046
(Sugishita laughing)

431
00:21:12,046 --> 00:21:14,048
That's totally ridiculous.

432
00:21:14,048 --> 00:21:15,133
Well, in any case, Ryouko,

433
00:21:15,133 --> 00:21:18,843
why don't we go do some
royal coupling of our own?

434
00:21:18,843 --> 00:21:19,721
What about it, huh?

435
00:21:19,721 --> 00:21:20,513
Do I look stupid?

436
00:21:20,513 --> 00:21:22,682
- [Sugishita] Hey, just
look at my sparkling eyes!

437
00:21:22,682 --> 00:21:24,267
- [Ryoko] They look
bloodshot to me.

438
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:25,560
- [Sugishita] That's
because you're throwing

439
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:26,852
dust in them, baby.

440
00:21:26,854 --> 00:21:30,854
- [Momiji] Let's see,
what happened after this.

441
00:21:30,854 --> 00:21:34,026
Oh, yeah, Yukiko and
I both started school.

442
00:21:34,026 --> 00:21:35,153
Momiji!

443
00:21:35,253 --> 00:21:39,253
- [Momiji] Isn't that great?

444
00:21:44,816 --> 00:21:48,816
The stuff really hits the fan!

445
00:21:48,816 --> 00:21:51,503
Mr. Sugishita, this
isn't a joke anymore.

446
00:21:51,603 --> 00:21:55,603
I may be as cute as a princess
but Kusanagi as a prince?

447
00:21:55,661 --> 00:21:59,661
No way, I refuse to
even think about it!

448
00:21:59,661 --> 00:22:00,678
Oh, now look what you've done!

449
00:22:00,764 --> 00:22:04,764
After you said that stupid
thing, I'm having a nightmare!

450
00:22:04,764 --> 00:22:05,475
What?

451
00:22:05,475 --> 00:22:06,768
This isn't a dream?

452
00:22:06,768 --> 00:22:09,061
Does that mean I'll become that?

453
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:13,161
It's the next episode of Blue
Seed, episode number eight.

454
00:22:13,161 --> 00:22:13,941
What?

455
00:22:13,941 --> 00:22:14,983
How strange!

456
00:22:14,983 --> 00:22:16,528
A rival appears!

457
00:22:16,628 --> 00:22:20,628
You mean, I'm gonna
be an idol singer?

458
00:22:30,458 --> 00:22:34,458
(singing in a foreign language)

